cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.CL, cs.CE 

The paper discusses the use of deep learning, specifically graph convolutional networks, for predicting molecular properties. This falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The use of attention and gate mechanisms also suggests a focus on natural language processing (cs.CL) and computer vision (cs.CV) subfields, which often utilize similar techniques. Finally, the application of the model to molecular engineering and drug discovery suggests a potential fit for computational biology (cs.CE).
